Apple Watch Sport Sport model is shown to shatter easily after being dropped from a height of just under four feet (1.2 metres)
Screen is held in an anodised aluminium case, which is 60 per cent stronger than standard aluminium, but is just as light as standard aluminium .
When the watch was dropped so the display hit the ground first, the screen shattered instantly .
Damage to the screen, such as chips, is not covered by the watch's warranty .